{"id":457,"date":"2022-03-29T17:10:32","date_gmt":"2022-03-29T17:10:32","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/parcos-project.eu\/?page_id=457"},"modified":"2023-06-13T10:24:39","modified_gmt":"2023-06-13T10:24:39","slug":"train-the-trainers-package","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/parcos-project.eu\/train-the-trainers-package\/","title":{"rendered":"&#8220;Train the Trainers&#8221; package"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<h2>Introduction<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Trainer Card deck is a <strong>reflection<\/strong> tool and contains <strong>guidelines<\/strong> for the <strong>design<\/strong>, <strong>iteration<\/strong>, and <strong>evaluation<\/strong> of science stories. The guidelines on the cards are posed in the form of questions to stimulate thinking and spark discussion. The questions on these cards are based upon quality criteria for science dissemination that were generated by a systematic review.\u200b<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The cards are characterized by three properties, including dimensions, layers, and themes.\u200b<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>There are four science story dimensions in the card deck. The dimensions correspond with four different facets of science storytelling, namely: \u201cscience\u201d, \u201ccommunication\u201d, \u201ctechnological tool\u201d, and \u201cimpact\u201d.\u200b<\/li><li>Within each dimension, we distinguish three layers that are ordered according to its complexity. These are ranging from the basic layer \u201clayer 1\u201d, the intermediate layer \u201clayer 2\u201d, to the most advanced layer \u201clayer 3\u201d.\u200b<\/li><li>Within each dimension and at each layer, there are one or more theme-specific content cards. \u200b<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Download the materials<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The card deck cutouts and the manual are available for download below.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can find an&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/miro.com\/app\/board\/uXjVOLvkiXk=\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">interactive, web-based version in Miro<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-file\"><a href=\"https:\/\/parcos-project.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Trainercards_Flattened-1.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Download the card deck as a printable PDF<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/parcos-project.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/Trainercards_Flattened-1.pdf\" class=\"wp-block-file__button\" download>Download<\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-file\"><a href=\"https:\/\/parcos-project.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/ParCos-trainer-manual.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Download the users manual of the Trainer Cards<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/parcos-project.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/ParCos-trainer-manual.pdf\" class=\"wp-block-file__button\" download>Download<\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Citation<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Van Even P., Zaman B. and Hannes K. (2022). ParCos Trainer update report. Deliverable 4.4 of the Horizon 2020 project ParCos, EC grant agreement no 872500, Lappeenranta, Finland.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Introduction The Trainer Card deck is a reflection tool and contains guidelines for the design, iteration, and evaluation of science stories. The guidelines on the cards are posed in the form of questions to stimulate thinking and spark discussion. The questions on these cards are based upon quality criteria for science dissemination that were generated &hellip; <\/p>\n<p class=\"link-more\"><a href=\"https:\/\/parcos-project.eu\/train-the-trainers-package\/\" class=\"more-link\">Continue reading<span class=\"screen-reader-text\"> &#8220;&#8220;Train the Trainers&#8221; package&#8221;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v18.4.1 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>&quot;Train the Trainers&quot; package -<